analysis.summary:
IPC streaming model. Three sketches against src/shared/ipc-contract.ts and src/main/ipc/router.ts (already supports `ipc:cancel` and `CallContext.signal`).

(i) one-shot `fs.searchText(query) -> SearchHit[]`: trivial; renderer passes `{signal}` and gets cancellation for free via existing src/renderer/ipc/client.ts. Cons: must buffer entire result set in main, no incremental UI, capped at e.g. 1k matches loses VSCode's progressive feel.
(ii) dedicated `search` channel with explicit `searchId` lifecycle: `call.start`+`listen.results`+`listen.done`+`call.cancel`. Mirrors VSCode's progress callback (`localFileSearch.ts:155 host.$sendTextSearchMatch`). Cons: two cancellation paths (signal vs. cancel call) duplicate the router's existing AbortController.
(iii) reuse the existing AbortSignal+requestId pattern, return `Promise<SearchComplete>` for the terminal stats, emit progress via `listen.progress({requestId, batch})`. Single cancellation surface (router already maps requestId→AbortController at router.ts:113-120). Backpressure: main awaits a microtask between batches; renderer drops late events whose requestId no longer matches the active session.

Recommend (iii). Concrete schemas:

```ts
const SearchOptionsSchema = z.object({
  pattern: z.string().min(1),
  isRegExp: z.boolean().default(false),
  isCaseSensitive: z.boolean().default(false),
  isWordMatch: z.boolean().default(false),
  includes: z.array(z.string()).default([]),
  excludes: z.array(z.string()).default([]),
  maxResults: z.number().int().positive().max(20000).default(2000),
  maxFileSize: z.number().int().positive().default(MAX_READABLE_FILE_SIZE),
});
const SearchRangeSchema = z.object({ line: z.number().int().nonnegative(), startCol: z.number().int().nonnegative(), endCol: z.number().int().nonnegative() });
const FileMatchSchema = z.object({ relPath: z.string(), matches: z.array(z.object({ range: SearchRangeSchema, preview: z.string() })) });
const SearchProgressSchema = z.object({ requestId: z.string(), batch: z.array(FileMatchSchema) });
const SearchCompleteSchema = z.object({ filesScanned: z.number().int(), matchesFound: z.number().int(), limitHit: z.boolean(), elapsedMs: z.number() });
// fs.call.searchText: args = { workspaceId, query: SearchOptionsSchema }, result = SearchCompleteSchema
// fs.listen.searchProgress: SearchProgressSchema  (batch up to 50 files OR 200 matches OR every ~30ms)
```

Backpressure policy: emit a batch when (a) batch.length >= 50 files, (b) cumulative matches >= 200, or (c) >=30ms since last emit. Drop on renderer side if `requestId !== activeRequestId` (workspace switch / new query).

Renderer state shape — `useSearchStore` mirrors src/renderer/state/stores/files/store.ts (Map<workspaceId,T> + cleanup registration) and src/renderer/state/lifecycle/workspace-cleanup.ts.

```ts
type SearchStatus = "idle" | "running" | "done" | "error";
interface FileGroup { relPath: string; matches: { range: SearchRange; preview: string }[]; expanded: boolean }
interface SearchSession {
  query: string;
  options: TextSearchOptions;        // isRegExp, isCaseSensitive, isWordMatch, includes, excludes
  results: FileGroup[];              // appended via batches; preserves insertion order
  status: SearchStatus;
  limitHit: boolean;
  filesScanned: number; matchesFound: number;
  requestId: string | null;          // active in-flight id; batches whose requestId mismatches are dropped
  controller: AbortController | null; // lives in session, NOT in the React tree — abort on re-query / workspace remove
  errorMessage?: string;
}
interface SearchState {
  sessions: Map<string, SearchSession>;       // by workspaceId
  startSearch: (wsId: string, opts: TextSearchOptions) => void;
  cancelSearch: (wsId: string) => void;
  appendBatch: (wsId: string, requestId: string, batch: FileMatch[]) => void;
  finishSearch: (wsId: string, requestId: string, complete: SearchComplete) => void;
  toggleGroup: (wsId: string, relPath: string) => void;
  closeAllForWorkspace: (wsId: string) => void;
}
```

Persistence policy:
- Preserve across mode switches (Files-panel ↔ Search-panel ↔ other tabs): `query`, `options`, `results`, `status`, `limitHit`, `filesScanned`, `matchesFound`. UX should re-render last results immediately on returning, matching VSCode's search view behavior.
- Reset on each new `startSearch`: `results`, `limitHit`, counters; abort prior `controller` first.
- Reset on workspace-removed: full `sessions.delete(workspaceId)` via `registerWorkspaceCleanup((id) => get().closeAllForWorkspace(id))` mirroring stores/files/store.ts:10-12.
- Reset on workspace-switch (active workspace change, NOT remove): keep the session — it lets users return to prior search results. Active workspace is not part of this store.

Cancellation flow: `startSearch` creates `new AbortController()`; passes `signal` via `ipcCall("fs","searchText", args, { signal })` (uses src/renderer/ipc/client.ts which routes through `ipc:cancel`). Re-issuing a query aborts the previous controller before creating the new one. `closeAllForWorkspace` aborts any in-flight controller during cleanup so main releases its walker. The `appendBatch` reducer no-ops when `requestId !== session.requestId` so late batches from a cancelled query never mutate state.

